<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-682] &lt;skipTests&gt; cannot be overridden by commandline param</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-682</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue is very similar to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-319&quot; title=&quot;&amp;lt;skip&amp;gt;true&amp;lt;/skip&amp;gt; cannot be overridden using mvn -Dmaven.test.skip=false test&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SUREFIRE-319&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SUREFIRE-319&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When &amp;lt;skipTests&amp;gt; is defined in the pom, there is no way to override the value using -DskipTests or -DskipTests=true|false on the command line.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think it would be better if command line parameter could have higher priority over pom configuration.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
